      "claim_id": "claim-e343c7dc82d7",
      "correctness_label": "partially_true",
      "load_bearing_label": "yes",
      "flip_evidence_text": "(A) effect a Change of Recommendation (1) if an (x) unsolicited, bona fide written Acquisition Proposal is received by the Company and has not been withdrawn or (y) Intervening Event has occurred, and (2) the Company Board determines in good faith, after consultation with outside legal counsel, that a failure to effect a Change of Recommendation would be inconsistent with the directors’ fiduciary duties under applicable Law and, in the case of an Acquisition Proposal contemplated by clause (A)(1)(x) of this Section 6.02(d)(iii), after consultation with its financial advisor, that such Acquisition Proposal constitutes a Superior Proposal; and/or (B) cause or permit the Company or any of the Company’s Subsidiaries to enter into an Alternative Acquisition Agreement with respect to a Superior Proposal... provided, however, that no such actions may be taken unless and until: (I) the Company has given Parent written notice at least four Business Days in advance... (II) during the Notice Period... negotiate in good faith... and (III) at the end of the Notice Period... determined in good faith... that a failure to effect a Change of Recommendation would continue to be inconsistent with the directors’ fiduciary duties under applicable Law, or that such Alternative Acquisition Agreement... continues to be... with respect to a Superior Proposal",
      "notes": "Omits that COR requires an unsolicited bona fide written Acquisition Proposal (not withdrawn) or an Intervening Event; omits mandatory consultation with outside legal counsel and financial advisor; misattributes the fiduciary-duty determination as the explicit standard for entering into an Alternative Acquisition Agreement; and omits the notice-period, good-faith negotiation, and Agreement-termination prerequisites."
    }
  ]
}

